  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ABColombia Group is a coalition of five UK and Irish development agencies (CAFOD, Christian Aid, OXFAM GB, Trocaire, SCIAF), with a Programme and Advocacy Manager based in Romero House. Amnesty International and Peace Brigades International participate in the group as observers. ABColombia aims to coordinate advocacy and information among the British and Irish agencies working on Colombia.  
ABColombia seeks to influence decision makers in the UK and Ireland and, through them, international / intergovernmental level decision making with a view to resolving the human rights and humanitarian crisis in Colombia and achieve a lasting peace and equitable and sustainable development.

PLEASE DO NOT CLOSE THIS PROJECT AS IT CAN BE USED FOR AN EXTENDED NUMBER OF YEARS TO FACILITATE THE ACCOUNTING TREATMENT OF HOSTING ABColombia.</narrative>
